    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offensive engine is well-positioned for today's slate, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker**. **Gunnar Henderson** claims the highest efficiency score at 81.87, buoyed by a favorable matchup against Wacha and a 10% boost for anchoring the top of the lineup. The combination of wind blowing out and a 15% skill edge against the starter makes him an elite play. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** (78.04) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.26) represent high-ceiling options; **Jackson Merrill** in particular benefits from a substantial 14% park factor upgrade, while **Kyle Tucker** maintains strong core projection despite a slight park penalty in his contest against Tyler Mahle. We are also capitalizing on aggressive platoon deployments for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (67.09), both of whom receive double-digit efficiency bumps from their respective lineup placements and platoon advantages.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was excluding **Marcell Ozuna** (59.51). While he holds a solid projected floor, the volatility of a \"Lineup Pending\" status combined with the current efficiency of our starting utility spot held by **Miguel Vargas** tipped the optimizer toward maintaining the current lineup structure. We are comfortable keeping **Marcell Ozuna** on the bench to preserve game caps, as his score sits just below our \"Strong\" start threshold. We have flagged **Andy Pages**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Miguel Vargas** as \"Lineup Pending,\" meaning their output relies on them maintaining their projected spots. While **Liam Hicks** (44.88) provides the lowest efficiency among our starters today, he remains in the lineup to cover the C1 slot, though he will be the first candidate for pinch-hit scenarios should the game script turn against us early.",
